														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-509054">
									

<p>Hi all who replied.</p>
<p>After a long period to calm down, I'd like to apologize for reacting the way I did. Horror is supposed to bring up a strong reaction and, obviously, mission freaking accomplished; even seriously twisted and disturbing things like this have literary merit, so and as long as there are clear NSFW<sup>1</sup>/NSFSS<sup>2</sup>/NSFAPCSWYR<sup>3</sup> warnings wherever the permanent link to this gets posted, there's nothing wrong with it being here. It's not like this is required reading, after all.</p>
<p>Anyway, I'm sorry for flipping out and I'll try not to do it again.</p>
<p><span style="font-size:xx-small;">1 - Not Safe For School<br />
2 - Not Safe For Sensitive Stomachs<br />
3 - Not Safe For Anywhere People Can See What You Read</span></p>

